00:24:14.276 --> 00:24:15.516 A:middle
So even though I'm looking

00:24:15.516 --> 00:24:17.786 A:middle
directly to the device it looks

00:24:17.786 --> 00:24:19.136 A:middle
as if somebody's watching me

00:24:19.136 --> 00:24:19.846 A:middle
from up above.

00:24:21.336 --> 00:24:22.516 A:middle
Now the reason we call this a

00:24:22.516 --> 00:24:25.076 A:middle
point cloud is if I zoom in you

00:24:25.076 --> 00:24:27.366 A:middle
can actually see the points in

00:24:27.366 --> 00:24:28.156 A:middle
3-D space.

00:24:28.686 --> 00:24:32.016 A:middle
But being here with you in WWDC

00:24:32.466 --> 00:24:33.576 A:middle
I feel like I have to pinch

00:24:33.576 --> 00:24:35.666 A:middle
