00:24:45.076 --> 00:24:47.396 A:middle
Thank you so that brings us to

00:24:47.936 --> 00:24:48.446 A:middle
point clouds.

00:24:48.446 --> 00:24:49.306 A:middle
How do we create them?

00:24:50.126 --> 00:24:51.426 A:middle
We're starting from a depth map,

00:24:51.826 --> 00:24:54.236 A:middle
a 2-D image in which the depth Z

00:24:54.716 --> 00:24:55.886 A:middle
is a function of the pixel

00:24:55.886 --> 00:24:57.056 A:middle
coordinates U and V.

00:24:58.486 --> 00:25:00.076 A:middle
And we want to transform it to a

00:24:58.486 --> 00:25:00.076 A:middle
And we want to transform it to a

00:25:00.076 --> 00:25:01.586 A:middle
new coordinate system in 3-D

00:25:01.586 --> 00:25:03.486 A:middle
space, X, Y, Z.

00:25:04.336 --> 00:25:06.256 A:middle
Now we already have Z right,

00:25:06.256 --> 00:25:07.616 A:middle
that's the depth from the depth

00:25:07.616 --> 00:25:09.766 A:middle
map but we want to get X and Y.

00:25:10.416 --> 00:25:13.606 A:middle
For that we need to get the help

00:25:13.606 --> 00:25:15.806 A:middle
from the Intrinsics Matrix which

00:25:15.806 --> 00:25:17.196 A:middle
holds information for the focal

00:25:17.196 --> 00:25:18.346 A:middle
lengths and principle point.

00:25:19.376 --> 00:25:21.686 A:middle
If for example I want to get X I

00:25:21.686 --> 00:25:22.936 A:middle
need to start with the pixel

00:25:22.936 --> 00:25:24.506 A:middle
coordinate U, subtract the

00:25:24.506 --> 00:25:26.576 A:middle
principle point, multiply by the

00:25:26.576 --> 00:25:28.576 A:middle
depth, and divide by the focal

00:25:28.576 --> 00:25:28.916 A:middle
lengths.

00:25:29.136 --> 00:25:30.416 A:middle
And naturally I have to do the

00:25:30.416 --> 00:25:31.256 A:middle
same thing for the other

00:25:31.256 --> 00:25:32.026 A:middle
dimension as well.

00:25:33.196 --> 00:25:36.976 A:middle
Now this Intrinsics Matrix is

00:25:36.976 --> 00:25:38.436 A:middle
accessible through the camera

00:25:38.436 --> 00:25:39.126 A:middle
calibration data.

00:25:39.716 --> 00:25:43.656 A:middle
In fact, this operation is done

00:25:44.786 --> 00:25:46.676 A:middle
in every frame of the TrueDepth

00:25:46.676 --> 00:25:47.056 A:middle
stream.

00:25:47.506 --> 00:25:49.836 A:middle
The reason for that is that the

00:25:49.836 --> 00:25:51.656 A:middle
video stream and the depth

00:25:51.656 --> 00:25:53.076 A:middle
stream are coming from two

00:25:53.286 --> 00:25:54.506 A:middle
separate cameras.

00:25:55.136 --> 00:25:57.246 A:middle
But because the TrueDepth camera

00:25:57.246 --> 00:25:58.936 A:middle
gives us a depth map we can

00:25:58.936 --> 00:26:00.446 A:middle
transform it into a point cloud

00:25:58.936 --> 00:26:00.446 A:middle
transform it into a point cloud

00:26:00.876 --> 00:26:03.046 A:middle
and re-project it to the

00:26:03.046 --> 00:26:06.306 A:middle
perspective of the RGB image so

00:26:06.306 --> 00:26:07.756 A:middle
the depth stream is already

00:26:07.756 --> 00:26:10.076 A:middle
registered on the video stream

00:26:10.076 --> 00:26:13.556 A:middle
for you and you get RGBD data.

00:26:14.146 --> 00:26:15.916 A:middle
Now, thank you.

00:26:16.496 --> 00:26:18.346 A:middle
Yeah, it's pretty cool.

00:26:20.066 --> 00:26:21.526 A:middle
Now these types of operations

00:26:21.626 --> 00:26:23.456 A:middle
are best done in metal graphic

00:26:23.456 --> 00:26:23.906 A:middle
shaders.

00:26:24.226 --> 00:26:25.476 A:middle
And you can download the code

00:26:25.476 --> 00:26:27.066 A:middle
for TrueDepth Streamer and you

00:26:27.066 --> 00:26:28.666 A:middle
want to focus on two areas.

00:26:29.196 --> 00:26:32.286 A:middle
In the vertex shader we control

00:26:32.286 --> 00:26:33.296 A:middle
the location of the points,

00:26:33.486 --> 00:26:34.976 A:middle
we'll start with the depth map

00:26:35.126 --> 00:26:36.696 A:middle
and transform it to real-world

00:26:36.696 --> 00:26:37.986 A:middle
coordinates or X, Y, Z.

00:26:39.186 --> 00:26:40.796 A:middle
Then we can multiply it with a

00:26:40.796 --> 00:26:43.006 A:middle
view matrix to change the point

00:26:43.006 --> 00:26:43.706 A:middle
of view to the scene.

00:26:44.336 --> 00:26:49.066 A:middle
In the fragment shader we get

00:26:49.066 --> 00:26:51.766 A:middle
the output of the vertex, but we

00:26:51.766 --> 00:26:53.866 A:middle
have to see if it's a real value

00:26:54.096 --> 00:26:55.186 A:middle
or a hole in the depth map.

00:26:56.026 --> 00:26:57.476 A:middle
If it's a hole and it's marked

00:26:57.476 --> 00:26:59.766 A:middle
as zero we don't know its depth

00:26:59.766 --> 00:27:01.516 A:middle
so we cannot transform it to X,

00:26:59.766 --> 00:27:01.516 A:middle
so we cannot transform it to X,

00:27:01.516 --> 00:27:02.856 A:middle
Y, Z and we would need to

00:27:02.856 --> 00:27:03.816 A:middle
discard this point.

00:27:05.196 --> 00:27:06.786 A:middle
If it is a real value we can

00:27:06.786 --> 00:27:09.286 A:middle
sample the RGB texture and add

00:27:09.286 --> 00:27:11.366 A:middle
color to the fragment or point

00:27:11.366 --> 00:27:14.746 A:middle
in this case.

00:27:14.956 --> 00:27:17.356 A:middle
So I understand this part was a

00:27:17.356 --> 00:27:19.066 A:middle
bit technical and a lot of you

00:27:19.066 --> 00:27:20.276 A:middle
come from different backgrounds.

00:27:21.016 --> 00:27:22.876 A:middle
Have no fear we have just the

00:27:22.876 --> 00:27:25.056 A:middle
app for you, an app to replace

00:27:25.056 --> 00:27:26.756 A:middle
your background, let's see it

00:27:26.756 --> 00:27:26.906 A:middle
live.

00:27:38.046 --> 00:27:40.926 A:middle
Let's see it live.

00:27:41.136 --> 00:27:43.516 A:middle
So I can put myself in Yosemite,

00:27:43.936 --> 00:27:46.466 A:middle
I can swipe down put myself in

00:27:46.466 --> 00:27:47.466 A:middle
something more abstract.

00:27:48.166 --> 00:27:51.466 A:middle
I can even go all the way to

00:27:51.466 --> 00:27:53.006 A:middle
Antelope Canyon, Arizona, it

00:27:53.006 --> 00:27:54.356 A:middle
took me 15 hours to get there

00:27:54.356 --> 00:27:55.846 A:middle
last time, I could have just

00:27:55.846 --> 00:27:57.426 A:middle
swiped down, saved a lot of

00:27:57.426 --> 00:27:58.126 A:middle
money on gas.

00:27:59.546 --> 00:28:02.016 A:middle
In fact, this application can

00:27:59.546 --> 00:28:02.016 A:middle
In fact, this application can

00:28:02.016 --> 00:28:04.116 A:middle
even put you in space where

00:28:04.116 --> 00:28:05.876 A:middle
nobody can hear you stream.

00:28:11.516 --> 00:28:15.616 A:middle
